<plot>'Women work for Barbie' is a two minute film short by London based artists Wyllie O Hagan. Wyllie O Hagan reflect on the irony of how global economics affect women. The video makes a simple statement about women who work in Barbie factories to make and to buy objects that shape children's image of self.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?660094</url></doc>
